doc/source/configuration/shared-file-sys.message:
Hi Goutham,

Sorry for the late response.

In Unity, when new share/filesystem created, some additional disk will be reversed for metadata storing, so in Unity driver, some additional disk will be added, for the share which size < 1.5GB, it will be added to 3GB, for the others, 1.5GB additional disk will be added. actually customer doesn't know the changes. When the customer creates a 2GB share, the share size is 2GB in OpenStack, in Unity, the corresponding share size is 3.5GB.

this is the source code:
def supplement_filesystem(old_size, user_cap=False):
    """Return new size accounting for the metadata."""
    new_size = old_size
    if user_cap:
        if old_size <= _GiB_to_Byte(1.5):
            new_size = _GiB_to_Byte(3)
        else:
            new_size += _GiB_to_Byte(1.5)
    return int(new_size)

For your suggestion, to implement the get_default_filter_function method in Unity driver, it will cause another issue, if the cloud only contains Unity backends, the <3GB share will no longer be created.

So my changes in the doc are not accurate. But the description above is too detail for the customer to read, so I think maybe I shuold abondon this change, what do you think?

Thanks

